13/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Adriean Videanu, Democratic Party (PD) vice president and mayor of Bucharest, will run for his party's presidency during a party congress next month.
Videanu confirmed his intentions on Thursday (12 May) and said he considers interim PD president Emil Boc and Interior Minister Vasile Blaga his most likely rivals for the leadership post.
The PD is a partner in the ruling coalition.
